      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/51/3",
      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ سَاقَ هَدْياً وَ لَمْ يُقَلِّدْهُ وَ لَمْ يُشْعِرْهُ قَالَ «قَدْ أَجْزَأَ عَنْهُ مَا أَكْثَرَ مَا لاَ يُقَلَّدُ وَ لاَ يُشْعَرُ وَ لاَ يُجَلَّلُ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2572 - Mu'awiyah ibn Ammar narrated from Abu Abdullah (as) regarding a man who drove a sacrificial animal but neither garlanded it nor marked it.\nImam (as) said: \"It is sufficient for him. Most often, sacrificial animals are neither garlanded, marked, nor adorned.\""
        ]
      }
    },
